    <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
      <p>Hoover Rupert was senior minister of the First United Methodist Church of Ann Arbor, Michigan. He served from 1959 to June of 1972. While in Ann Arbor, Rupert was active in civic affairs and community leadership. He was a leader in the efforts to secure a Fair Housing Ordinance in Ann Arbor. Rupert was also an author, writing fifteen books and a syndicated magazine column.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
      <p>The collection is comprised almost entirely of drafts of his writings and other materials relating to publication of his writings. There is also an extensive run of his published sermons.</p>
    </scopecontent>
